description:
&lt;p&gt;The post will cover Patient Meal Services at both Hull Royal Infirmary (HRI) and Castle Hill Hospital (CHH).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will be working various shifts to cover service delivery requirements. The department operates from 06:00 through to 18:30 7 days a week including public holidays, the above posts will predominantly work the below shift times:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will assist in the provision of a comprehensive and cost-effective catering service that meets the needs of all patients whilst fulfilling the objectives of the Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To provide a full range of high quality ward catering services including the regeneration and attractive presentation of a wide range of cook-freeze food items.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties will include the preparation, storage, packaging, distribution, regeneration and service of patient meals. Regularly handling frozen, chilled and cooked food items whilst standing for prolonged periods of time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ensure all patient meals are accurate and served in a timely manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To undertake a wide range of general kitchen and catering hygiene duties at ward level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To work in accordance with Food Hygiene Regulations, Codes of Practice for Caterers and all relevant Trust policies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to demonstrate good customer/patient care skills, and have a basic knowledge of food service and food hygiene.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexibility to work between Castle Hill Hospital and Hull Royal Infirmary is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: The role does involve physical work in an area with varying temperatures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;** Salary relates to year 3 of 3 year NHS pay deal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joanne Tock, Patient Meals Team Leader Joanne.Tock@hey.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adriana Verschoor, Patient Meals Team Leader Adriana.Verschoor@hey.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Elizabeth Hatch, Patient Meals Team Leader Elizabeth.Hatch@hey.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
